# 🧠 OS Concept 2: Distributed Retries & Idempotency

🔥 Important reliability concept.

---

# 🔹 Retries

If request fails temporarily:

👉 retry automatically.

---

## Problem

Retrying can accidentally duplicate operations.

Example:

```text id="2n7qvw"
Payment processed twice
```

Dangerous ❌

---

# 🔹 Idempotency

Same request repeated multiple times:

👉 result remains same.

---

## Example

Setting:

```text id="9k3xzp"
status = completed
```

multiple times is safe.

---

## 🧠 Real-World Analogy

Pressing elevator button repeatedly doesn’t create multiple elevators.

---

## Why Important?

Critical for:

✔ payment systems
✔ distributed APIs
✔ retries

---

## 🎯 Placement Question

**Q: Why idempotency important in distributed systems?**

👉 Because retries may occur during failures, and duplicate actions must be avoided.

---

## 🧠 Memory Trick

```text id="6v1qmn"
Repeat safely without side effects
```

---

# ⚙️ COA Concept 3: Reconfigurable Computing (FPGAs)

🔥 Advanced hardware interview topic.

---

## 1️⃣ Simple Idea

FPGAs are chips whose hardware behavior can be reprogrammed after manufacturing.

---

## FPGA =

Field-Programmable Gate Array

---

## Why Useful?

Can customize hardware for:

✔ AI
✔ networking
✔ signal processing
✔ acceleration tasks

---

## 🧠 Real-World Analogy

LEGO blocks rearranged into different machines.

---

## Difference from CPU

CPU:

General-purpose fixed architecture.

FPGA:

Customizable hardware logic.

---

## 🎯 Placement Question

**Q: Why FPGAs are powerful?**

👉 Because hardware can be customized for specific workloads.

---

## 🧠 Memory Trick

```text id="5p9xrk"
FPGA = programmable hardware
```

